Package uk.ac.aston.coursework.elevator.objects

Class Elevator

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.aston.coursework.elevator.objects.Elevator
  • public class Elevator
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents an Elevator. It can move between floor 0 to n number of floors, accepting requests from up and down buttons in each floor.

    nisat

    • Constructor Detail

      • Elevator

        public Elevator​(Building building)
        This constructor constructs a Direction class which is used to represent the direction of the elevator. It also constructs a HashSet of people called elevatorSet which is used to represent the people inside elevator. It also constructs an ArrayList of integer called targetFloors. This is used to store the floor numbers that require the elevator.
        Parameters:
        building -

        Returns:
        true if the person exists in the elevator.

      • enterElevator

        public void enterElevator​(Person p)
        This method adds Person p to elevator provided they have enough space. Their target floor is added to targetFloors ArrayList as if they pressed a button inside the elevator to go to a specific floor.
        Parameters:
        p - is the person that needs to enter the elevator.

      • leaveElevator

        public void leaveElevator​(Person p)
        This method removes Person p from the elevator.
        Parameters:
        p - p is the Person that needs to be removed from elevator.

      • goToFloor

        public void goToFloor​(int floor,
                      boolean forStandby)
        This method moves up or down a floor one by one until floor is reached.
        Parameters:
        floor - is the floor that the elevator needs to go to.
        forStandby - used for printing on console only once.
